Given an integer N, write a program to find the sum of the first and last digit in the absolute value of N.
Input Format

A single integer N
Constraints

-10^9 <= N <= 10^9
Output Format

Print a single integer â€” the sum of the first and last digit.
Sample Input 0

12345
Sample Output 0

6
Explanation 0

First digit = 1, Last digit = 5, sum = 6

Sample Input 1

-907
Sample Output 1

16
Explanation 1

First digit = 9, Last digit = 7, sum = 16

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        if(n<0){
            n=-n;
        }
        int last=n%10;
        int first=n;
    while(first>=10){
        first=first/10;
    }
    int sum=first+last;
    System.out.println(sum);
    }
}
